      <lg xml:id="TolE0463">
<l>oṉpāṉ mutaṉilai muntukiḷan taṟṟē</l>
<l>muntai yoṟṟē ḷakāra miraṭṭu</l>
<l>nūṟeṉ kiḷavi nakāra meykeṭa</l>
<l>ūvā vāku miyaṟkait teṉpa</l>
<l>vāyiṭai varuta likāra rakāra</l>
<l>mīṟumey keṭuttu makara moṟṟum</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>The initial of <foreign xml:lang="ta">oṉpāṉ</foreign> [will have the alteration] mentioned before ;</l>
<l>the preceding consonant becomes <foreign xml:lang="ta">ḷ</foreign> [and is] doubled, the word</l>
<l><foreign xml:lang="ta">nūṟu</foreign> will lose the consonant <foreign xml:lang="ta">n, ū</foreign> changes into <foreign xml:lang="ta">ā</foreign> -thus it is said ;</l>
<l><foreign xml:lang="ta">ī</foreign> and <foreign xml:lang="ta">ra</foreign> occurs in the middle at that place, and the final [part of</l>
<l><foreign xml:lang="ta">nūṟu</foreign>] disappears, replaced by <foreign xml:lang="ta">m.</foreign></l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
